HEADWORD: Misalliance
<hw>Mis`al*li"ance</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>m⟦eacute⟧salliance</ets>.]</ety> <def>A marriage with a person of
inferior rank or social station; an improper alliance; a
mesalliance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A Leigh had made a <qex>misalliance</qex>, and blushed⟦br⟧
A Howard should know it.</q> <rj><qau>Mrs. Browning.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Misallied</ent>⟦br⟧
